io.github.retrooper.packetevents.event.eventtypes

Class NMSPacketEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.retrooper.packetevents.event.PacketEvent
      • io.github.retrooper.packetevents.event.eventtypes.NMSPacketEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CallableEvent
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CancellableNMSPacketEvent, PostPacketPlayReceiveEvent, PostPacketPlaySendEvent

    public abstract class NMSPacketEvent
extends PacketEvent
implements CallableEvent
    The NMSPacketEvent abstract class represents an event that has to do with an actual packet. Don't mix this up with PacketEvent. The PacketEvent class represents an event that belongs to PacketEvent's packet system.
    Since:
    1.8

      • getPacketName

        @Deprecated
public final java.lang.String getPacketName()
        Deprecated. 
        This method returns the NMS name of the packet. To get the name of the packet we get the class of the packet and then the simple name of the class. See also: Class.getSimpleName() We cache the name after the first call to improve performance. It is not recommended to call this method unless you NEED it. If you are comparing packet types, use the PacketType byte system. You would only need the packet name if packet type system doesn't contain your desired packet yet.
        Returns:
        Name of the packet.
